TODAY'S APPETIZER
QUENELLES OF SALMON
Finely chopped boneless filets of salmon are lightly seasoned,
blended with cream and egg whites, then poached in
court bouillon. Served with fresh dill.
TOSSED GREEN SALAD, MONTICARL DRESSING
A crispy mix of romaine, chicory and iceberg lettuce is tossed with
mushrooms, bean sprouts, tomato wedges, marinated red peppers
and Monticarl Dressing.
YOUR CHOICE
OCEAN TO OCEAN SPECIALTY
CIOPPINO
Fisherman's Wharf in San Francisco serves a popular and familiar
Italian seafood dish called Cioppino. Our version combines
Alaskan king crab, shrimp, scallops and clams with a
tomato and wine sauce blended with saffron and
Italian spices. Served with Cheese Bread.
COQ AU VIN
Chicken breast and thigh are sauteed in butter with pearl onions
and mushrooms. Braised until tender and served with a
rich white wine sauce, egg noodles, and green peas
with sliced carrots.
OUR LIGHTER AIR FARE
It is as satisfying, but not quite as filling as our more
elaborate entrees. Today we offer:
FRESH FRUIT PLATE GARNI
An array of fresh fruits in season tastefully arranged and
served with cottage cheese.
ROAST STRIP SIRLOIN OF BEEF, AU JUS
We start with USDA Choice sirloin of beef, rub it with herbs and
spices, then roast it in its natural juices. This favorite will be
carved at your seat ... for the perfect accompaniment try
our mild horseradish sauce.
